# Retro pre-save summary format

Compact preview shown to the user before writing the retrospective file. Goal: enough to judge framing and decide Save / Refine / Cancel — not the full body.

Render in chat (markdown), in this order:

## 1. Header

`Retro summary — {plan-kebab-title}` (or `{retro-kebab-title}` for multi-plan).

## 2. Verdict line

One paragraph. Cross-plan verdict word (`success` / `partial` / `fail`) + the load-bearing sprint stats: SP total, commit count + short SHAs, planned-to-completed elapsed time, milestone DoD pass rate, Final Verification pass rate. Stats only — no narrative.

## 3. What went well

Bulleted list, 3–6 items. Each bullet names a concrete decision, move, or outcome — not a feeling. Reference specific commits, sections, or lessons by id where it sharpens the point.

## 4. Issues

Markdown table with columns: `#`, `Issue`, `Cause`, `Impact`, `Lesson touched`.

- One row per accepted issue from Phase 2b.
- `Issue` — short noun phrase (the *what*).
- `Cause` — one-sentence root cause (the *why*).
- `Impact` — one-sentence consequence (the *so what*); cite earlier retros / instances if this is a recurrence.
- `Lesson touched` — `lessons/NNNN_*.md` path if any, else `—`.

If there are zero accepted issues, render `_No accepted issues._` instead of an empty table.

## 5. Action items

Markdown table with columns: `#`, `Action`, `Owner`, `Status`.

- One row per follow-up the user agreed to in Phase 3.
- `Action` — concrete imperative move; specify scope (file, plan, decision).
- `Owner` — `User`, `Claude`, or a named role.
- `Status` — `Planned`, `Planned (carried over)` for items rolled from a prior retro, or `Done` if completed in-session.

If there are zero actions, render `_No action items._` instead of an empty table.

## 6. Takeaways

Bulleted list, 2–4 items. Each takeaway is a transferable rule of thumb the user might apply to future plans of this shape — not a restatement of an issue. If a takeaway only repeats an action item or a "what went well" bullet, drop it.

## Hard rules

- No frontmatter, no save path, no commit command — those belong in Phase 5, after the user confirms.
- No candidate lessons section — `/learn` owns that surface.
- Do not exceed ~40 lines of rendered output. If the body is bigger, the summary is wrong shape.
